{"key":"post-18572266","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>18572266</id>\n<content>If the yield is equal from the top or sides, what does it matter?&amp;nbsp; The fact is, the mycelium fruits where it wants to, not where it's best for us.&amp;nbsp; There's usually as much or nearly as much surface area around the edges as there is on the whole top, depending on depth of substrate.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As an added benefit, once the substrate shrinks due to &lt;i&gt;being consumed by mycelium&lt;/i&gt;, you can pour water around the edges to rehydrate it easily.&amp;nbsp; Some of the biggest monster mushrooms posted here grew from the edges of the substrate, not the top.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It's also a function of strain sometimes in that despite our best efforts at surface moisture management, often they just fruit around the edges anyway. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/shrug.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:shrug:&quot; title=&quot;:shrug:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>18572759</next>\n<prev>18572164</prev>\n<first>18563973</first>\n<last>18572851</last>\n<when>1374100832</when>\n<utime>07/18/13 01:40 AM</utime>\n</post>"}